methods.samelineBlock:
The tail wagging the dog: the proper method signature for this method is
 CodeGenerator samelineBlock(String prefix, Object... args) But when I do that, IntelliJ by default
 litters up the code with parameter hints, which (if the programmer doesn't turn them off), makes the templated
 code much more unreadable. So instead we just pull out the parameter from here.

:param args: (java.lang.Object...) - A prefix (of type String) like "else", followed by an arbitrary number of template lines.
:return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.impl.util.codegen.CodeGenerator) The new component.
